div1.p: In reapplication of Ching Hing for a Writ of Habeas Corpus.

Now on this day the Petitioner comes into open Court to apply for Writ of Habeas Corpus. Albert Moody appearing for the Government and on motion of counsel for the Government, and statements that counsel for the petitioner has consented thereto, hearing on the application herein is continued to October 16, 1914, at 2.00 P.M.
In the matter of the application of Ching Hing for a Writ of Habeas Corpus.

Now on this day this cause on for hearing, Geo. F. Fishburne, appearing for the Respondent and John J. Sullivan appearing for Petitioner, on motion of the Petitioner it is now ordered that said hearing be and the same is hereby continued until Oct. 30, 1914, at 2.00 o'clock P.M.
